        <item xml:lang="zh">使正式就職</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">立／封</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>APPOINT to an IMPORTANT RANK.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general term for installing someone in a high position is lì 立.</p>
<p>2. Fēng 封 refers specifically to installing a person in an enfeoffed position.</p>
<p>3. Jiàn 建 primarily refers to the establishment not of a person but of the position itself; however, the word does occasionally refer to the establishment of a person in the position of a ruler.</p>
<p>NB: Jí wèi 即位 and the rarer as well as more elevated jiàn zuò 踐阼 refer to the act of ascending the throne, i.e. to "being installed".</p>
        </div>
